Progress in Photovoltaics is a monthly peer-reviewed scientific journal covering research on photovoltaics. It is published by John Wiley & Sons and the editor-in-chief is Martin A. Green (University of New South Wales). According to the Journal Citation Reports, the journal has a 2013 impact factor of 9.696, ranking it 4th out of 83 journals in "Energy & Fuels", 9th out of 136 journals in "Physics Applied", and 15th out of 251 journals in "Materials Science Multidisciplinary".
